<html lang="en" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <title>Kinect Game Configuration</title>
    <style type="text/css"/>
</head>
<body>
    <h1 class="top">One more thing...</h1>
    <p>
        To run this project, you will need to <strong>install additional 
        dependencies</strong> using <strong>easy_install</strong>.
    </p>

    <h1>Install required packages</h1>
    <ol>
        <li>
            Download pygame, available at <a target="_blank" href="http://www.lfd.uci.edu/~gohlke/pythonlibs/#pygame">http://www.lfd.uci.edu/~gohlke/pythonlibs/#pygame</a>.
        </li>
        <li>Open Solution Explorer.</li>
        <li>
            <p>Right-click on the Python environment and select Install Python Package.</p>
            <img src="InstallPythonPackage.png" />
        </li>
        <li>
            <p>
                In the combo box, select easy_install. In the text box, type the
                full path to the pygame executable, in double-quotes.
            </p>
            <img src="InstallPygameDialog.png" />
        </li>
    </ol>

    <blockquote>
        <p>
            If you get an error installing pygame, you can try installing from
            the command line from your environment's python.exe folder:
        </p>
        <code>python.exe -m easy_install "path to pygame exe"</code>
    </blockquote>
</body>
</html>